title: Sample Book, Decorator-Styled Wallpaper, 1955–60
description: A large variety of designs with most shown in multiple colorways. The papers include patterns for all rooms of the home including kitchen and bathroom papers, and papers for children and teens. There are wood grain, moiré and rough plaster effects.  A collection of ceiling papers is shown at the end. All designs are very traditional in nature.  All are roller printed, with some being embossed.  Papers are shown with their coordinates.

tombstone.epitaph: Sample Book, Decorator-Styled Wallpaper, 1955–60; Manufactured by Sears, Roebuck and Co. (United States); USA; machine-printed and embossed; 47 x 47 cm (18 1/2 x 18 1/2 in.); 1964-55-1-1/195
